    Functions to scrape olympic data

    scrape.Rd

    Functions to scrape olympic data from olympic.com

    get_sports(game)

get_single_event(url)

get_events(table)

get_single_result(url)

get_results(table)

    Arguments

    game

    used in get_sports();
    in the format of tokyo-2020, see the slug column in the built-in data olympic_game.

    url

    used in get_single_event() and get_single_result();
    the URL to the sport/ event page, see examples.

    table

    used in get_events() and get_results();
    the tibble produced by get_sports() and get_events(), see examples.

    Value

    a tibble of event summary

    Examples

    # sport table in Tokyo 2020
get_sports(game = "tokyo-2020")
#> # A tibble: 46 × 2
#>    game       sport                
#>    <chr>      <chr>                
#>  1 tokyo-2020 wrestling            
#>  2 tokyo-2020 weightlifting        
#>  3 tokyo-2020 water-polo

#>  6 tokyo-2020 trampoline-gymnastics
#>  7 tokyo-2020 tennis               
#>  8 tokyo-2020 taekwondo            
#>  9 tokyo-2020 table-tennis         
#> 10 tokyo-2020 swimming             
#> # … with 36 more rows

# event table from URL or sport table

# event results from URL or event table
url <- "https://olympics.com/en/olympic-games/tokyo-2020/results/swimming/women-s-800m-freestyle"
get_single_result(url)
